# Kith portfolio — core rules

Single scrollable one-page portfolio. Five sections, scroll order: Hero → Experience → Competitions → Work → Contact. Each has its own structural metaphor — never reuse one section's card/layout pattern in another.

## Source of truth
- `/reference/*.html` prototypes are the source of truth for ANIMATION and motion. Do not reinvent easing, timing, or scroll mechanics — port them faithfully.
- `/reference/*-spec.md` are the source of truth for intent, layout, copy, and colour.
- Motion conflict → prototype wins. Intent/content conflict → spec wins.

## Stack
- Next.js App Router + TypeScript. Plain CSS: global tokens (CSS vars) + one CSS Module per section. NO Tailwind. Fonts via `next/font`.

## Design tokens (locked — do not alter)
- Display: **Barlow Condensed** 700/800, italic for display use.
- Mono/utility: **IBM Plex Mono** 300/400. Prose (where proportional): **IBM Plex Sans**. Work labels: **Oswald** 400. Work taglines: **DM Sans** italic. Competitions handwriting: **Caveat**.
- Accent: `#6BAED6` (UNC powder blue). Darker sibling (Work ink): `#1f5d80`.
- Dark bg `#0f1014` · borders `#1e2535` · warm light/paper `#f0eeea` · cork `#b8845a`.
- Palette rhythm across sections: dark → dark → cork → paper → dark.
- Wordmark: "KITH" in a thin border box, with the dot OUTSIDE the box in accent colour.

## Motion tokens
- Opens/expands: `cubic-bezier(0.16, 1, 0.3, 1)`.
- Polaroid flip: `cubic-bezier(0.23, 1, 0.32, 1)`. Stack spring: `cubic-bezier(0.34, 1.15, 0.64, 1)`.
- Text reveals: monospace character scramble, ~700ms, left-to-right sweep (labels/names); slideUp from clip mask (headlines); typewriter (Contact definition only).

## Non-negotiable behaviors
- Scroll-scrubbed transforms are IMPERATIVE: one shared `requestAnimationFrame` loop writing `transform`/`opacity` via refs. NEVER drive per-frame scroll animation through React state.
- Scroll reveals re-fire on EVERY entry and reset on exit. Never `unobserve()` after the first trigger; reset opacity/transform/text when elements leave the viewport.
- Before triggering a CSS transition from a just-set start transform, force reflow with `getBoundingClientRect()` — otherwise the browser batches the writes and skips the start state.
- Always honour `prefers-reduced-motion`: show final states, skip scrubbed motion, never trap the user in a pinned scroll.

## Taste guardrails
- Cut anything that reads as generic or AI-generated (filler labels, "Solo · 8 wks" context lines, boilerplate microcopy). If a line could be on any portfolio, remove it.
- Prefer rendered results over descriptions; keep each section's metaphor structurally distinct.
